title.narrative: COMMUNICATION FOR DEVELOPMENT (C4D)

description.narrative: Enhanced capacities of countries to use evidence based Communication for Development (C4D) strategies to empower communities, adolescents and civil societies and create demand for high impact interventions in both development and humanitarian settings, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: ESAR Country Offices programmes are evidence-based, results-oriented, affordable, fit for purpose and represent value for money by 2021

title.narrative: Enhanced capacities of countries to use evidence based C4D strategies to empower communities, adolescents and civil societies and create demand for high impact interventions in both development and humanitarian settings

description.narrative: Countries received support to strengthen the use of evidence-based strategies in at least one of the following areas: reproductive, maternal, newborn, child and adolescent health (RMNCAH), Early Childhood Development, Birth Registration, Demand for Immunization, Social Accountability, Harmful practices and social norms, adolescent participation and development. A regional C4D network meeting allowed ESAR countries to exchange learning and good practices. In addition, a 3-day orientation meeting allowed to build knowledge and capacity for new C4D staff from 8 COs. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/01/2020
